            "answer_text": "I upvoted several answers here including Rose Swan, Diagnosed NPD. The answer is yes. The last NPD I dealt with was very critical of my wife and my wife\u2019s family. He said my wife\u2019s family were losers without jobs and too lazy to work. He said they just sit around and wait for wealthy people in the US to send money. He claimed that I said this myself about my father-in-law. But he didn\u2019t realize my father-in-law died 6 years before I ever met my wife. He didn\u2019t realize that all of my wife\u2019s family works hard and is very self sufficient. I found out later that he sends his wife\u2019s family a rather large sum of money every month and that his father gave most of what he had to a girlfriend instead of helping his own family. I found out that most of his wife\u2019s family sits around and waits for him to send money every month. I also heard that they they don\u2019t think much of him except for his money (according to his wife\u2019s own words). He told me my wife was very greedy and lazy and criticized her work ethic. He also said that she was mean over and over again and said that she has no real feelings and fakes being hurt so she can get sympathy. He also said she is a huge gossip. I guess I now know how he sees his own wife. 99% of the criticism from an NPD is projection or DARVO (Deny, Accuse, Reverse Victim Offender). They are experts at role reversal and acting as though you are the one with the problem and they are sane. ",
